I hope this works out.

106
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,320
This isn't a movie.

107
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:11,450
You're not some kind of hero.

108
00:08:11,450 --> 00:08:13,550
Know your place!

109
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,050
What's wrong with that?!

110
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:19,960
I love pre-established harmonies, ideals,

111
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:22,950
rules, and even forced happy endings! {Mikado goes to rub-n-tugs}

112
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:26,000
What's wrong with desiring them?!

113
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:31,480
I'm not claiming that it's for the good of others or the world.

114
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,630
I just want to see it for myself.

115
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:35,490
I want to believe in that!

116
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:39,240
Yes... I will believe in that.

117
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,990
I will believe!

118
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:48,460
They all will...

119
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:53,670
I might be beating a dead horse,

120
00:08:53,670 --> 00:09:00,310
but that proves that people care about it!

121
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,930
Are you done?

122
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:22,330
I don't have the power and wisdom to make someone as ignorant as you to see reason.

123
00:09:22,330 --> 00:09:25,060
You won't even give me a chance to prove myself.

124
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:26,790
That's why...

125
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:34,090
I'll rely on others!

126
00:10:05,620 --> 00:10:07,370
What?!

127
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,380
Whoa!

128
00:10:17,380 --> 00:10:19,520
Is all that because of the cellphones?!

129
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,900
Awesome!

130
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,270
This is like the supernatural phenomenon from "Missing"!

131
